AmaXhosa King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu is being buried today in Willowvale in the Eastern Cape. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - AmaXhosa King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu is being buried today in Willowvale in the Eastern Cape. The King died earlier this month after a short illness. President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver the eulogy. READ: AmaXhosa king dies aged 51 King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu has been accorded a category 1 funeral. He had been King since January 2006. King Zwelonke Sigcawu was coronated in 2015 at Nqadu Great Place, the occasion marked the first coronation of a king in the amaXhosa nation in 50-years.